docs.name: PDMRX: Putnam Absolute Return 700 - R
docs.description:
The investment seeks to earn a positive total return that exceeds the rate of inflation by 700 basis points (or 7.00%) over a reasonable period of time regardless of market conditions.
 The fund combines two separate investment strategies. The beta strategy consists of a globally diversified asset allocation strategy. The alpha strategy involves the potential use of various 'overlay' strategies. These consist of diverse active trading strategies designed to provide additional total return through the exploitation of market inefficiencies and other conditions.

docs.name: LMTCX: Legg Mason Target Retirement 2035 Cl C

It seeks to achieve its objectives by investing in a combination of underlying funds representing a variety of broad asset classes-equity, fixed income and inflation-and investment styles. docs.name: 0895: DONGJIANG ENV
docs.description: Dongjiang Environmental Company Limited, together with its subsidiaries, operates in waste management and environmental service businesses. It offers inorganic salts, organic solvents, basic industrial oil, fatty acid series, and coating materials that are applicable in industries, such as animal feed, agricultural pesticides, wood preservatives, dyes, medicines, and construction coatings, as well as engages in the conversion of methane in landfill field gas into electricity. The company also provides a range of waste management and environmental solutions, including waste collection, treatment, and utilization; environmental engineering design; facilities operation; and environmental consultancy services. In addition, it offers treatment, reutilization, and disposal services through chemical, physical, and biological methods to a range of industrial hazardous wastes; and converts reusable contents from various types of wastes into useful products. Further, the company is involved in producing, trading, and selling chemical products; consulting environmental testing technology; laboratory testing activities; selling and purchasing zinc and copper wastes; collecting municipal domestic wastes; collecting and selling industrial wastewater; developing and utilizing landfill gas; investing and managing energy recycling projects; generating power from landfill gas; researching, promoting, and applying technologies of environmental products; producing negative electrode copper; managing properties; and transporting dangerous goods. It serves customers in various industries, including electronics, electroplating, machine manufacturing, chemical engineering, energy, and pharmaceutical. The company was formerly known as Shenzhen Dongjiang Environmental Company Limited and changed its name to Dongjiang Environmental Company Limited in December 2010. Dongjiang Environmental Company Limited was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Shenzhen, the Peoples Republic of China. Currency: HKD

docs.name: Wilshire US REIT ETF (WREI)
docs.description: Historical ETF prices for Wilshire US REIT ETF (WREI). Wilshire US REIT ETF (the Fund) seeks investment results that correspond generally to the performance of an equity index called the Wilshire US Real Estate Investment Trust Index (the Index). The Fund, using a passive or indexing investment approach, will seek to replicate the performance of the Index. The Index is a rules-based index consisting of securities of companies of all categories of market capitalizations as defined by Wilshire Associates Incorporated (the Index Provider). The Index consists primarily of real estate investment trusts (REITs) and is derived from the Wilshire 5000 Total Market Index. The Index is designed to serve as a proxy for direct real estate investment by institutions. The Index is weighted by float-adjusted market capitalization. The Fund will normally invest at least 80% of its total assets in equity securities that comprise the Index. Its investment adviser is Claymore Advisors, LLC. The Fund's sub-adviser is Guggenheim Partners Asset Management, LLC.

docs.name: Palatin Technologies, Inc. (PTN)
docs.description: Palatin Technologies, Inc. (Palatin) is a biopharmaceutical company engaged in the development of peptide, peptide mimetic and small molecule agonist compounds with a focus on melanocortin and natriuretic peptide receptor systems. As of June 30, 2010, the Company had three drug development programs, including Bremelanotide, Peptide melanocortin receptor agonists and PL-3994. Bremelanotide is a peptide melanocortin receptor agonist. PL-3994 is a peptide mimetic natriuretic peptide receptor A (NPR-A) agonist, for treatment of acute exacerbations of asthma, heart failure and refractory or difficult-to-control hypertension. The Company has licensed several families of melanocortin receptor-based compounds for treatment of obesity, diabetes and related metabolic syndrome to AstraZeneca AB (AstraZeneca).
